deliveryMessages: FREE delivery Wednesday, February 21 on orders shipped by Amazon over $35. Order within 2 hrs
features: [Say Goodbye to Mess]: Our car seat gap filler organizer is here to prevent small items from falling between the car seat gaps, keeping your car's interior tidy. It provides a handy car pocket to store essentials like change, cards, and phones, keeping them within easy reach.

[Premium Leather Material]: Our car gap organizer is made of high-quality PU leather that looks very luxurious and feels soft to the touch. Unlike plastic alternatives, the soft PU leather will not damage your seat leather.

[Easy to Install]: Simply insert the box into the gap between your seat and center console. It only takes a few seconds to install. The storage box stops items from dropping into the crevice area and creates additional storage space for cell phones, keys, coins, cards, wallets, and other small items. It helps keep your vehicle's interior space organized and cleaner.

[New Version and Size]: Unlike other brands, our leather car gap filler does not require adhesive to fix it in place. The dimensions of the gap filler are 11.81 x 1.38 x 7.87 inches (length, width, height), providing ample space for storage.

[Adjustability and Stability]: Our car gap organizer is designed to fit car seat gaps between 0.4" and 2", making it suitable for various car, truck, and SUV models. The foam insert between the seat and console is thick and flexible, providing a secure and stable fit to ensure it stays in place during your journey.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No more lost phone between the seat and console
reviews.reviewText: My 2023 GMC Terrain front car seats don't have a large gap between them and the center console but it's just wide enough for, yes, you guessed it, losing my phone. Even with a chunky phone case it manages to slip in between whenever it gets away from me in the car. And what a struggle to retrieve it. No more! Not with this handy gap filler - it's got a nice leather feel, easy to clean. And yeah, it also keeps that gap area free from dust and dirt too because it's difficult to get a vacuum in there. It's not deep enough to store much - I can fit my phone on it's side and would probably stow a wallet just fine but I'll probably use it for extra charging cables and paper receipts and stuff to keep my car from looking cluttered.
